abstract: Tennis has long been known for its prodigies — and the cautionary tales that many of them tell.
snippet: Tennis has long been known for its prodigies — and the cautionary tales that many of them tell.
lead_paragraph: WIMBLEDON, England — Tennis has its latest prodigy in Cori Gauff, the 15-year-old American who upset Venus Williams, once a wonder child herself, in the first round of Wimbledon of Monday.

abstract: It teaches music to children in troubled neighborhoods and helped its city heal after riots. But the Baltimore Symphony is in crisis.
snippet: It teaches music to children in troubled neighborhoods and helped its city heal after riots. But the Baltimore Symphony is in crisis.
lead_paragraph: BALTIMORE — When violent unrest spread through the streets of Baltimore in 2015 after the death of Freddie Gray, an African-American man who suffered a spinal injury while in police custody, the Baltimore Orioles took the extraordinary step of playing in an empty stadium, barring fans because of safety concerns.

abstract: President Trump’s elder daughter used a G20 summit and then the Demilitarized Zone to test her role as budding stateswoman for the administration.
snippet: President Trump’s elder daughter used a G20 summit and then the Demilitarized Zone to test her role as budding stateswoman for the administration.
lead_paragraph: Set against a tense, eerie silence in the landmine-riddled mountains separating South and North Korea, the Demilitarized Zone may be the highest-stakes negotiation site on earth. It’s not the sort of place for mistakes.

abstract: Mr. Buttigieg’s $24.8 million second-quarter total is the latest evidence that he has gone from a long shot to a serious candidate for the nomination in a matter of months.
snippet: Mr. Buttigieg’s $24.8 million second-quarter total is the latest evidence that he has gone from a long shot to a serious candidate for the nomination in a matter of months.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Pete Buttigieg’s top fund-raisers gathered in Miami Beach to watch the first Democratic debate last week, those in attendance included corporate executives, Chelsea Clinton’s wedding planner and a 19-year-old who had started a viral Facebook page supporting the South Bend, Ind., mayor’s presidential campaign.

abstract: But where do you draw the line? The Democratic candidates are contorting themselves trying to find the sweet spot.
snippet: But where do you draw the line? The Democratic candidates are contorting themselves trying to find the sweet spot.
lead_paragraph: How far to the left the Democrats are going has been a major topic of conversation in the first months of the contest for their party’s presidential nomination. One school of thought, which includes every Republican, holds that the Democrats have taken a sharp turn to the left and may be leaving some of the voters they need behind.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Sunday shrugged off the brutal dismembering of Jamal Khashoggi, a Washington Post columnist, just days after a United Nations report described how a team of Saudi assassins called Mr. Khashoggi a “sacrificial animal” before his murder.
